---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="HVAC Local Market Report | See Why Competitors Get More Calls | Built on Tenth"
  description="See why competitors are getting more HVAC calls in your city. The HVAC Local Market Report shows local visibility gaps, competitor pressure, and estimated missed-call loss in 48 hours."
  active=""
>
  

  <div class="page-shell">
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="page-wrap hero__grid">
        <div class="hero__copy">
          <h1>See exactly why your competitors are getting more HVAC calls <em>and where you’re losing them.</em></h1>
          <p class="hero__subline">
            We analyze your local HVAC market and show you missed calls, weak spots,
            and revenue gaps in one report, so you can stop guessing what is holding
            your market position back.
          </p>
          <div class="hero__actions page-actions">
            <a href="/report" class="btn btn--primary">Request your report</a>
            <a href="/tools" class="text-link">Explore HVAC calculators</a>
          </div>
          <div class="hero__micro">
            <span>No call required</span>
            <span>Delivered in 48 hours</span>
            <span>Built using real local data</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <aside class="hero-card">
          <div class="hero-card__top">
            <div class="hero-card__price">$200</div>
            <h2 class="hero-card__title">HVAC Local Market Report</h2>
            <div class="hero-card__meta">
              <span>Delivered in 48 hours</span>
              <span>Built using real local data</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <ul class="hero-card__list">
            <li>See the competitors taking more calls in your city</li>
            <li>Understand your real Google Maps visibility gap</li>
            <li>Get a missed-revenue estimate tied to the gap</li>
            <li>Know what to fix first if you want to close it</li>
          </ul>
          <div class="hero-card__foot">
            <a href="/report" class="btn btn--primary">Request your report</a>
          </div>
        </aside>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="problem-strip">
      <div class="page-wrap problem-grid">
        <article class="problem-card">
          <strong class="problem-card__value problem-card__value--blue">42%</strong>
          <h3>Visibility problems hide before the phone rings</h3>
          <p>If your local presence is weaker than the companies around you, the missed opportunity starts before your CSR even has a chance to book the call.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="problem-card">
          <strong class="problem-card__value problem-card__value--amber">$211</strong>
          <h3>Buying more leads is an expensive way to stay confused</h3>
          <p>Before you spend more on PPC or LSAs, it helps to know whether your local market position is the actual leak.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="problem-card">
          <strong class="problem-card__value problem-card__value--red">200+</strong>
          <h3>Trust gaps stack up fast in local HVAC markets</h3>
          <p>The top companies often combine review volume, profile strength, and visible activity in a way that quietly widens the gap every month.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="page-wrap">
        <div class="section-head">
          <div class="section-label">How it works</div>
          <h2>We scan your market, find where competitors are winning, and show you how to close the gap.</h2>
          <p>This should feel like analysis, not software onboarding. The goal is simple: give you a fast, credible answer before another month disappears into guesswork.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="steps">
          <article class="step-card">
            <div class="step-number">01</div>
            <h3>We scan your top competitors</h3>
            <p>We look at the companies homeowners actually see around your city for the keyword that matters most to your service business.</p>
            <span class="step-meta">Maps rankings + visible trust signals</span>
          </article>
          <article class="step-card">
            <div class="step-number">02</div>
            <h3>We find exactly where they’re winning</h3>
            <p>Review velocity, profile completeness, local visibility, and visible activity all get compared so the gap stops feeling abstract.</p>
            <span class="step-meta">Gap analysis, not generic SEO advice</span>
          </article>
          <article class="step-card">
            <div class="step-number">03</div>
            <h3>We show you how to close the gap</h3>
            <p>You get a report that explains what is happening, what it may be costing, and what deserves attention first if you want more calls.</p>
            <span class="step-meta">Delivered in 48 hours</span>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="proof">
      <div class="page-wrap proof-grid">
        <div class="proof-copy">
          <h2>When the gap is visible, the problem gets harder to ignore.</h2>
          <p>The report is meant to create that moment. You should be able to look at one page and immediately understand why other companies are getting the call first.</p>
          <ul class="proof-list">
            <li>Your exact ranking position vs the companies outranking you</li>
            <li>The local players stealing trust and visibility in your city</li>
            <li>The likely call opportunity you are missing while they stay ahead</li>
            <li>The short list of fixes most likely to move the needle first</li>
          </ul>
          <div class="proof-copy__bar">
            <span>Estimated monthly call gap in this example</span>
            <strong>+38 calls/mo</strong>
          </div>
        </div>

        <aside class="report-mock">
          <div class="report-mock__head">
            <span>HVAC Local Market Report</span>
            <span>Built on Tenth</span>
          </div>
          <div class="report-mock__body">
            <span class="report-mock__sample">Local market snapshot</span>
            <h3>Apex Comfort Systems</h3>
            <p>Dallas, TX · “AC repair Dallas” · Analyzed March 2026</p>
            <div class="report-mock__table">
              <div class="report-mock__row">
                <strong>Cool Breeze HVAC</strong>
                <span>4.9</span>
                <span>847</span>
                <span>#1</span>
              </div>
              <div class="report-mock__row">
                <strong>Texas Air Experts</strong>
                <span>4.8</span>
                <span>612</span>
                <span>#2</span>
              </div>
              <div class="report-mock__row">
                <strong>One Hour Heating</strong>
                <span>4.7</span>
                <span>439</span>
                <span>#3</span>
              </div>
              <div class="report-mock__row report-mock__row--you">
                <strong>Apex Comfort ← You</strong>
                <span>4.3</span>
                <span>91</span>
                <span>#4</span>
              </div>
              <div class="report-mock__row">
                <strong>Air Comfort Solutions</strong>
                <span>4.6</span>
                <span>318</span>
                <span>#5</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="report-mock__foot">
              <span>Estimated monthly calls going to top competitors</span>
              <strong>+38 calls/mo gap</strong>
            </div>
          </div>
        </aside>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section section--muted">
      <div class="page-wrap">
        <div class="section-head">
          <div class="section-label">What you get</div>
          <h2>Outcome-focused deliverables, not a pile of observations.</h2>
          <p>The report should help you decide what matters next. Every section exists to make the opportunity and the fix path more obvious.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="deliverables">
          <article class="deliverable-card">
            <div class="deliverable-number">01</div>
            <h3>Know exactly who is stealing your calls</h3>
            <p>See the local companies homeowners are most likely choosing over you, not a random list of competitors that do not matter.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="deliverable-card">
            <div class="deliverable-number">02</div>
            <h3>See your real ranking position vs competitors</h3>
            <p>Understand where you actually sit in the map pack for the service keyword that matters most in your city.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="deliverable-card">
            <div class="deliverable-number">03</div>
            <h3>Identify missed revenue instantly</h3>
            <p>Translate a local visibility problem into a business number that is easier to act on and harder to dismiss.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="deliverable-card">
            <div class="deliverable-number">04</div>
            <h3>Know what to fix first</h3>
            <p>Get ranked priorities based on likely impact, so you do not burn another month spreading effort across the wrong things.</p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="cta-card-section">
      <div class="page-wrap">
        <div class="cta-card cta-card--report">
          <div class="cta-card__inner">
            <h2 class="cta-card__title">See where your HVAC market is leaving you behind.</h2>
            <p class="cta-card__body">Request the HVAC Local Market Report and see why competitors are getting the calls you thought should be yours within 48 hours.</p>
            <div class="cta-card__actions">
              <a href="/report" class="btn btn--primary">Request your report</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</Layout>
